  "prompt": "What happens when a batsman hit a shot and ball hits the spidercam?",
  "response": "When a batsman hits the ball and it strikes the spidercam (the cable-suspended camera system used in cricket broadcasts), the result typically depends on the specific rules of the tournament being played. According to the International Cricket Council (ICC) playing conditions, if the ball hits the spidercam, it is generally considered a dead ball, and the delivery does not count. \n\nThe batsman is not dismissed, and any runs scored from that delivery are also not counted. The umpire will then reset the field for the next delivery. However, it's important to note that the interpretation and enforcement can vary by league or tournament, so it's always best to check the specific rules in effect for the particular match or competition.",
